==English==

===Noun===
'''grief'''
# [[Pain]] of mind on account of something in the past; mental [[suffer]]ing arising from any cause, as misfortune, loss of friends, misconduct of one's self or others, etc.; sorrow; [[sad]]ness.
#:''Her betrayal caused Jeff grief.''
# Cause of sorrow or pain; that which afficts or distresses; trial; grievance.
#:''She was worn out from so much grief.''
# Physical pain, or a cause of it; malady.
#:''My elbow has been giving me grief.''
# [[hassle]], [[abuse]]
#:''Fred was giving me grief over the money I owed him.''

